- Iran imposed new airspace restrictions on Saturday, May 23, during the American-Israeli war on Iran.
- A Notice to Air Missions identified as OIIX A1010/26 announced closure of airports across the western section of the Tehran Flight Information Region, with only a limited number of facilities permitted to operate during daylight hours.
- The restrictions were expected to remain in place until Monday, May 25.
- Airlines were required to seek fresh approval from Iran's Civil Aviation Authority before operating passenger flights in affected areas.
- The report placed the announcement amid heightened regional tensions and diplomatic activity involving Washington and Tehran.

